  "prompt": "Is a brain transplant theoretically possible?",
  "response": "A complete brain transplant is currently not possible and faces numerous scientific and ethical challenges:\n\n1. Technical difficulties:\n- Connecting the complex neural networks\n- Preventing tissue damage during transplant\n- Maintaining blood supply and nerve connections\n- Preventing immune rejection\n\n2. Ethical concerns:\n- Definition of personal identity\n- Consent and medical ethics\n- Potential psychological impacts\n\n3. Philosophical questions:\n- Would the recipient's personality remain intact?\n- Would memories transfer with the brain?\n\nWhile partial brain procedures like deep brain stimulation exist, a full brain transplant remains in the realm of science fiction. Current medical technology cannot successfully perform such a complex procedure.",
